                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding xml:id="binding" contemporary="true">
                                    <decoNote xml:id="b1" type="bindingMaterial">
                                      The book is bound in <material key="wood">wooden</material> boards covered with reddish-brown blind-tooled <material
                                      key="leather">leather</material>.
                                    </decoNote>
                                    <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="Boards">
                                      The boards are cut to the same size as the bookblock and present external shallow bevels.
                                      On the inner surface of the lower board, in the middle, remnants of a greyish substance are present,
                                      which perhaps was used to glue a <term key="mirror">mirror</term>.
                                    </decoNote>
                                    <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Cover" color="brown">
                                      Full brown leather cover, once red, as can be seen from the turn-ins.
                                      The turn-ins have been trimmed out, and they form butt mitres at the corners.
                                      An <term key="additionalLeatherPatch">additional leather patch</term> has been added along the inner margin of the boards to fill the gap between the turn-ins.
                                      The cover shows a fine blind-tooled decoration, identical on both sides of the cover. The turn-ins and the spine are also decorated.
                                      The decoration consists of three concentric frames surrounding a central rectangular panel featuring a diamond-shaped cross
                                      surmounted by a roof-like frame and above it a diamond shape.
                                      Frames composed by the repetition of single tools, enclosed between <term key="doubleStraightLine">double straight lines</term>,
                                      alternate with empty ones.
                                      Proceeding from the outer to the inner frame, the repeating decoration motifs are <term key="crissCross">criss-cross</term> and
                                      <term key="XForm">X-forms</term>.
                                      Dotted lines between double straight lines form the cross.
                                      At the ends of the arms of the cross there are four <term key="doubleCircle">double circles</term>.
                                      Groups of four double circles are also stamped at the intersections of the double straight lines.
                                      In the areas at the foot of the cross, the triple straight lines form two triangles, each surmounted by four double circles.
                                      Concentric frames of double straight lines decorate the turn-ins.
                                      On the spine, <term key="tripleStraightLine">triple straight lines</term> delimit four panels in which double straight lines cross each other diagonally, forming eight-pointed stars.
                                      In the middle of which, a double circle was stamped.
                                    </decoNote>
                                    <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Endbands">
                                      The endbands are missing but their turn-ins have been preserved.
                                    </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b5" type="SewingStations">4</decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b6">
                                  Chainstitch sewing on four sewing stations (two pairs); periodic fold pattern; Z-plied threads.
                                  Between each pair of sewing stations there are two thread lengths.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b7" type="Spine">
                                  At the head and tail are preserved the short horizontal stitches used to pierce the leather on the spine
                                  in two points (at the head and tail), thus fixing the endbands to the cover.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b8" type="SlipCase">
                                  The manuscript is provided with a leather two-piece single-walled slipcase with a hanging strap,
                                  which passes through two flaps on the bottom panels of both cases.
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote xml:id="b9" type="Other">
                                  Threads of various colours are inserted in the outer margins for navigating the text.
                                  More specifically, a red <term key="leafStringMark">leaf string marker</term> is inserted in the outer margin of <locus target="#4 #40 #109 #127 #145"/> and a
                                  green <term key="leafStringMark">leaf string marker</term> is inserted in the upper margin of <locus target="#10 #45 #64 #77 #104 #134"/>.
